<br>
I think ultimately this spell is worth while, and I will getting a stack of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>QoK</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to carry with me.<br>
<br>
I know I have been in situations where it would have been very useful to give to the melees.  Also, the ability to have essentially a second bind point seems worth while.<br>
<br>
Yes, I make and always carry a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Thurgadin Gate Potion</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
But <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>QoK</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is stackable and useable by others.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>TGP</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is no drop, and many players, even melees, do not understand the value of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>TGP</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
It also seems like it adds some groupability.<br>
<br>
